cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper introduces a new type of loop and special instructions for it, which is relevant to the study of programming languages.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper discusses the semantics of a new type of loop, which could be seen as a logical concept.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a new feature for programming languages, which is relevant to software engineering.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper introduces a new type of loop and provides two different semantic projections, which could be seen as formal language concepts.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the algorithmic adequacy of one of the semantic projections, which is relevant to the study of data structures and algorithms.
